Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a small #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the @basmati rice{1/4%cup} and stir continuously until grains are golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in remaining @basmati rice{1/4%cup} and @water{3/4%cup}. Bring to a boil, then cover and lower heat. Simmer until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Wash and dry all produce. Core, seed, and remove white ribs from @red bell pepper{1}(thinly sliced), then thinly slice. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}(whites and greens separated), keeping greens and whites separate. Cut @lime{1} into wedges. Drain @corn{1/2%can} from can.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper, scallion whites, garlic, and a pinch of @chili flakes{pinch}. Cook, tossing, until softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Rinse @shrimp{10%oz} and pat dry with a #paper towel{}. Once veggies are softened, add shrimp to pan. Cook, tossing, until opaque and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and add to pan, along with corn, scallion greens, @soy sauce{1%tbsp}, and @sesame oil{1/2%tbsp}. Cook, tossing, until everything is evenly mixed and soy sauce is absorbed, about ~{1%minute}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice mixture between bowls. Garnish with @peanuts{1%oz}. Serve with lime wedges on the side for squeezing over.